com.basho.riak.client.api.cap

Interface ConflictResolver<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the objects to be resolved.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultResolver

    public interface ConflictResolver<T>
    Interface used to resolve siblings.

    When you have multiple writers there may be multiple versions of the same object stored in Riak. When fetching all of these will be returned and you will need to resolve the conflict.

    To facilitate this, you can store an instance of the ConflictResolver in the ConflictResolverFactory for a class. It will then be used by the FetchValue.Response to resolve a set a of siblings to a single object.

    Since:
    2.0
    Author:
    Brian Roach
